Classification: PUBLIC



Dear Geeta,



Please provide us as requsted as it is insured duty to provide as per the terms and conditions of policy. We need to know the estimate/quantum of claim in order to appoint surveyors.



Again please provide as below 



1.       Estimation of loss to consider appointment of surveyor; 

2.       Attached claim form to be duly completed;



The rest of the below at later stage:



3.       Copy of insured relevant certificate to register the claim;

4.       Suppliers Invoice issued prior to shipment highlighting / identifying the claimed items;

5.       Packing list and delivery receipt with remarks;

6.       Evidence of transit damage (Customs damage report/ Stevedores damage report / EIR);

7.       Claim submitted to the responsible parties holding them liable and inviting them for a joint survey (include proof of sending / acknowledgement and reply, if received);

8.       Documents showing if the cargo was unloaded from container for customs inspection at the port;

9.       Appointment/ contact details/ location for a joint survey;

10.    Arrival date, date of discharge from vessel; Date of customs inspection; Date/place damage noted; 

11.    Attached claim form to be duly completed;



Best 



